    text: "— re\nROOKE’S REPLY TO ALLENS\nCARD—-WHAT HARRY HILL\nHASTO SAY-ROOKE BLOWa-\nING HIS BAZOO AGAIN.\n‘The Irish Giant on the War Path.\n| [Special to the St. Louis Dispatch. |\nNEw York, June 22.—In reply to a card\nof Tom Allen's, in which he states that he re-\ntires from the ring, Rooke, who wants to\nfight, says: ‘Allen, in announcing his re-\ntirement from the ring, has scen fit to make\nan unjustifiable assanlt upon Ben. Hogan and\nmyself. My match with Allen was for 1,500\na side, to be fought June 17. Harry Hill was\ntemporary stockholder, and the final stock-\nbolder was to be agreed on. Mr. John Cham-\nAeriain was selected. Through a misunder-\nstanding between Allen and Harry Hill, in re-\ngard to the money alleged to be due\nto the latter, a delay todk place in\nthe transfer of the stakes to Mr. Chamberlain\nand he refused to act.\n\nJames Collier was mutually agreed upon,\nbut declined, and after ineffectual attempts to\nagree, the friends of Allen and my represen-\ntatives declared the match off. I telegraphed\nthat the match was off, in conformity with\nthe articles of agreement, through the failure\nto agree on a stakcholder. I was prepared to\nrenew any amount, or to fight him for the\nchampionship without a dollar. After these\nvotices and with the knowledge that he\nwould be alone in the ring, Allen went to the\nground, stepped into the ring and claimed the\nstakes. We could not meet on the\nseventeenth under our old articles\nof agreement, and he knew I wanted a new\nmatch. He knew I wonld not be in the ring.\n\nJluowing all this he threw in his cap, showed\nLis own bravery, accused me of cowardice and\nran away. I now ask Mr. Tom Allen to test\nbis own and my courage by fighting me with-\nout stakes. If he accepts I will bet him one\nthousand dollars that I whip him, which will\npay Lis expenses, should he be vietorious.™\n\nHARRY HILL'S STATEMENT.\n\nHarry Hill savs: “The late failure to decide\nthe issue of Allen vs, Rooke in the roped\narena, makes it my duty, beo-\ning the temporary stake-lwlder of\n=3.000. made dependent thereon, to notify pub-\nLicly all parties having a money interest there-\nwu, to pre=ent their claims, either in person or\nby proxy for prompt adjudication aud scttle-\nnent. on or after Monday, June the 25th in-\nstant\n\nHAREY'S OPINION,\n\nHe believes that both men made the mateh\n\n: good faith, that both were anxions to fight,\nAud Lut for the untimely interference of par-\nties interested in the monetary issue would\nunguestionably have fought out the issue to\nthe bitter end. both being courageous and\nskillful men. He says Rooke is anxious to\nficht Allen, and =o are Coburn and\nHogan, and that Allen ought to\ntizlit to decide the question and then retire.",
