    text: "THEY AKE UNDER ARREST\nAnd Charged With Robbing a Sleeping\nStranger in Market Street Saloon.\n\nThomas Barrett and George Ohls are under\narrest at the Central District Police Station\ncharged with petit larceny.\n\nJames St. John is a young man whose home\nis at Sulphur Springs, Mo. He fell asleep in\nTom Allen’s saloon, 619 Market street, yester-\nday. When he awoke about 10 o’clock last\nnight he found that his watch and chain,\nwhich he had purchased but a few hours be-\nfore had been stolenefrom his pocket.\nHe at once notified Allen of his loss and the\nlatter called In Sergt. Shoemaker and\nOfficer Carr, to whom he gave a description\nof two men who had been seen hanging about\nthe place that night. Barrett and Ohls were\nfound on an adjacent corner and placed under\narrest.\n\nWhile Officer Carr went across the street to\ncall the patrol wagon Sergt. Shoemaker re-\nmained in charge of the men. He noticed\nBarrett acting in a suspicious manner. Fin-\nally Barrett drew something from his pocket\nand threw it in the ailey. The Sergeant picked\nit up and recognized the missing watch, St.\nJohn identified his property this morning and\na warrant charging Barrett with petit larceny\nWas sworn out.\n\nBoth of the prisoners are badly crippled.\nOhls is minus his left arm, which he sald he\nhad crushed between the bumpers of two\nfreight cars while switching In Kansas City.\nBarrett had his right leg broken some ten\nweeks ago in a saloon on Market street. He\nwas released from the City Hospital on last\nWednesday.",
