    text: "THE RING,\n\nTom Allen, America’s ex-champion heavy-\nwelght was the biggest Mitchell shouter ila St\nLouls when the tricky Englishman fought the\nchampion at Chantilly, France. Tom was\nalso a Killrain man when Jake met defeat at\nthe hands of John L. at Richburg, Miss., two\nyears ago. Charlie Mitchell, who 1s one of\nAllen's eg Irlends, was responsible,\nMitchell had fought Sullivan and secunded\nKilrain when he rought Smith and trained\nJake for his battie with the champion. Tom\nthought he ouzht to have a good line and\nbacked Kilrain on Mitchell’s judgment. This\ntime the old ex-champion 1s with Sullivan\n\n, and will back him whenever an opportunity\npresents itself.”’\n\nJack McAuliffe and George Dixon will All\nout Allen’s combination. The old ex-cham-\npion will leave st. Louls for the Cres-\ncent Clty next sunday morning, ac-\ncompanied hy r red Watkins, his\nold backer, Billy Dacre, ‘Tom Riley,\n“*Nobby’’ Clarke and Chris Louff. The crowd\nwill have plenty of discussion on the way\ndown, for, though they are all Sulifvan\nmen, opinion among them is dl-\nvided on the Mver-McAuiiffe battle,\n“*NODbLY’’ Clarke and Chris l.auff are red-hot\nMyer men and will back the ‘‘Streator\nCyclone’’ at even money {if need be. Clarke\nhas placed $75 against $100 already, but can-\nnot get any more at the same terms in this\ncity. He expects to be accommodated when |\nthe New York contingent, who are all\n\nMcAuliffe men, reach New Orleans.",
