    text: "WHY ALLEN IS A MITCHELL MAN.\nThe Ex-Champion Sure Birmingham\nFighters Are the Fest in the World.\nTom Allen says emphatically that Charlie\nMitchell must win against Champion Jim\nCorbett, and the more the ex-champion says\nit the more he thinks it. Now, according to\nJoseph Donovan, Allen Is not to be denied,\nand while It may be a trifle cruel, {it\nshould be mentioned in order to fully pro-\ntect those who might be disposed to give\nAllen's opinion some little weight, knowing\nas they do he anclently carried prestige him-\nselfas a fighter, that, first, Tom Allen was\nborn in Birmingham, and, secondly, so was\nCharles Mitcheil, and Tom arrived at the\nconclusion some years ago from a subtle sort\nof reasoning, which he has never vouchsafed\nto make public, that as sure\nas the sun rises and sets a man born\nin Birmingham can always lick a man\nnot born in Birmingham. It was figuring\nalong the lines of this ratiocinative process\nthat actuated Tom to back Ed Smith, a Bir-\ngen man agalnst Joe Goddard, when\n\ne whole country, ‘‘Denver’’ Ed probably\nincluded, couldn’t see a ghost of a show\nahead. Tom didn’t know anything about\nGoddard's doing himself wrong beyond the\nad at which he could traln properly anda\nurthermore he didn’t care. The fact that\nSmith was originally from Birmingham and\nGoddard was not was all-sufficient and Tom\npiled his winning shekels high. Now, as\nmight have been expected, Tom is back with\nhis winnipg system in regard to the inter-\nnational contest.",
