    id: "165",
    text: "\"ALLEN TO BACK AIM\n——e\nNeist Challenges Moomey for a\n. Wrestling Match.\nTHE RETIRED CHAMPION TO FURNISH\nHIS SIDE STAKE OF $250.\n\nThe Match to Be at the Lightweight\nLimit, Any Style and the Winner to\nTake All-Purse Offered in London for\nCraig and Choynski or Creedon—\nSporting News and Gossip.\n\nTom Allen, the retired champion, an-\nnounces his willingness to back Al. J. Neist\nagainst Mike Mooney, in a wrestling match\nany style, at the light-weight limit, for $250\na side. Neist is a boxer and wrestler, and\nhe is anxious to meet Moomey at either\ngame, ;\n\n“There is no chance to pull off a fight\nin any kind of shape around St. Louis now-\nadays, however,” said Allen, “and for that\nreason, I advised Neist to try and get\nMooney to wrestle him, ‘I have great con-\nfidence in Neist, and with proper handling\nhe will be a hard man to beat at his weight.\nWe have $250 ready to put up, any time\nMooney feels like making a match, and the\nwinner can take all, including the gue re-\nceipts. Neist doesn’t want a cent if he can't\nwin, and if Mooney wants a match, now is\nhis chance. He can have either style—\nGraeco-Roman or catch-as-catch-can. All\nwe shall stipulate is that he get down 10\nthe light-weight limit, and as he claims to\nbe in that class, both as a boxer and\nwrestler, we expect no kick from him on\nthis point. Mooney, by the way, has done\nmore challenging and less boxing and wrest-\nling than any man in St. Louis, veg cy 3 the\nvast vear. If he is as anxious to do busi-\n1ess as he would have the public believe,\ne should not hesitate any in accepting\nNeist’s challenge. We are ready to post\nour stake at any time,and Neist will wrestle\nwithin four weeks of signing articles.”",
