    text: "HE THOUGHT IT FUN.\nMatthew Groves Pulls Chairs From Un-\nder the Wrong Men at the Wrong Place.\nMathew Groves, aged 40, who claims to\nlive at 115 North Second street, but who is\nsaid to be a “hanger-on’'” at Tom Allen's\nsaloon on Market street, near Seventh,\nwalked into the Four Courts Friday morn-\ning at an early hour with a badly swollen\njaw. He said he had been asaulted without\nprovocation in Allen's saloon. Inquiry by\nthe police revealed the fact that Groves\nwent into the saloon among a lot of the\n“chair-warmers’” and pw <r to amuse him-\nself by pulling chairs from under them.\nAndrew Flynn, the bartender, first re-\nquested Groves to stop, and when this had\nno effect he went up to Groves and landed\nhis +, gy on the latter's jaw, fracturing it\nslightly, No arrest was made. Groves\n\nwas sent to the City Hospital.",
