    text: "i Sn ce iri. + a ERE\n| Ui . : § Ait 1)\nNO DIVORCE FOR HOUSEXEEPET\nan WEYL\nDecree Denied to Tillie Hartgrove\nWhen Judge Learned She Had\nServed Tom Allen.\n\nWhen Judge Taylor learned from the last\nwitness in the suit of Mrs. Tillle Rartgrove\nagainst Martin Hartgrove for divorce that\nthe plaintiff had been the housekeeper of\nthe {ate Tom Allen, he curtly denied ths\ndecree.\n\n| Mrs. Hartgrove testified that her hus.\nband, to whom she was married seven vears\nago, deserted her less than two weeks aft.\ner the wedding. She sald she had SUD\n, ported herself ever since.\n| Before Allen died it was announced that\n| he Ly Be a the Ee Steg ahe obe\ni taln er divorce. e wil his propert\n| to her for her services. -\n| Allen's estate, which has dwindled ale\njonah to nothing, is still in litigation.\n) i ———",
